# ================================================================
# notify CLI - Environment Configuration
# ================================================================
#
# This CLI supports multiple notification providers. Configure ONE
# provider below. The CLI auto-detects which provider to use based
# on which environment variables are set.
#
# Provider Priority (first configured wins):
#   1. Pushover  (PUSHOVER_USER + PUSHOVER_TOKEN)
#   2. ntfy.sh   (NTFY_TOPIC)
#   3. Twilio    (TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID + TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN)
#   4. Email     (EMAIL_USER + EMAIL_PASS + SMS_CARRIER)
#
# ================================================================


# ================================================================
# OPTION 1: Pushover (RECOMMENDED)
# ================================================================
# Cost: $5 USD one-time per platform (iOS, Android, or Desktop)
# Pros: Reliable push notifications, works on locked phone, 10k msgs/month free
# Cons: Requires one-time purchase
#
# Setup:
#   1. Download the app:
#      - iOS: https://apps.apple.com/app/pushover/id506088175
#      - Android: https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=net.superblock.pushover
#   2. Create account: https://pushover.net
#   3. Copy your User Key from the dashboard (shown after login)
#   4. Create an Application: https://pushover.net/apps/build
#      - Name it "notify" or whatever you like
#      - Copy the API Token/Key it generates
#   5. Paste both values below and uncomment:

# PUSHOVER_USER=uQiRzpo4DXghDmr9QZgQ2Ty7wGkPfh
# PUSHOVER_TOKEN=azGDORePK8gMaC0QOYAMyEEuzJnyUi


# ================================================================
# OPTION 2: ntfy.sh (Free, Open Source)
# ================================================================
# Cost: Free
# Pros: No account required, open source, self-hostable
# Cons: iOS app uses polling (no real push - must have app open)
#       Android works great with real push notifications
#
# Setup:
#   1. Install the app:
#      - iOS: https://apps.apple.com/app/ntfy/id1625396347
#      - Android: https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=io.heckel.ntfy
#   2. Open the app and subscribe to a topic (e.g., "my-alerts-xyz123")
#      - Use a unique topic name - anyone who knows it can send to it
#   3. Paste your topic name below and uncomment:

# NTFY_TOPIC=my-alerts-xyz123

# Optional: Use a self-hosted ntfy server instead of ntfy.sh
# NTFY_SERVER=https://ntfy.example.com


# ================================================================
# OPTION 3: Twilio (Traditional SMS)
# ================================================================
# Cost: ~$20 to start + ~$5.50 for A2P registration + ~$0.01/SMS
# Pros: Real SMS messages, professional, reliable
# Cons: Requires A2P 10DLC registration for US numbers (1-7 day approval)
#       Trial accounts cannot complete registration
#       Complex setup process
#
# Setup:
#   1. Create account: https://www.twilio.com/try-twilio
#   2. Upgrade to paid account (add $20 minimum)
#   3. Buy a phone number (~$1.15/month)
#   4. Complete A2P 10DLC registration:
#      - Register as Sole Proprietor (~$4 one-time)
#      - Register a Campaign (~$1.50/month)
#      - Link your phone number to the campaign
#      - Wait 1-7 days for approval
#   5. Get credentials from https://console.twilio.com
#   6. Paste values below and uncomment:

# TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID=ACxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
# TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
# TWILIO_PHONE_NUMBER=+14155551234


# ================================================================
# OPTION 4: Email-to-SMS Gateway (Free, Unreliable)
# ================================================================
# Cost: Free
# Pros: No registration, uses your existing email
# Cons: Many carriers block these messages (especially AT&T)
#       Requires knowing recipient's carrier
#       Messages may be delayed or never arrive
#
# Setup:
#   1. Use a Gmail account (recommended)
#   2. Enable 2-Factor Authentication: https://myaccount.google.com/security
#   3. Generate an App Password: https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords
#      - Select "Mail" and "Other (Custom name)"
#      - Copy the 16-character password (remove spaces)
#   4. Paste values below and uncomment:

# EMAIL_USER=your-email@gmail.com
# EMAIL_PASS=abcdefghijklmnop
# SMS_CARRIER=att

# Supported carriers:
#   att        - AT&T (often blocked)
#   tmobile    - T-Mobile
#   verizon    - Verizon
#   sprint     - Sprint
#   uscellular - US Cellular
#   boost      - Boost Mobile
#   cricket    - Cricket Wireless
#   metropcs   - Metro PCS
#   virgin     - Virgin Mobile

# Optional: Use a different SMTP server (defaults to Gmail)
# EMAIL_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
# EMAIL_PORT=587
# EMAIL_SECURE=false


# ================================================================
# Provider Comparison
# ================================================================
#
# | Provider     | Cost          | Reliability | Setup Time | Notes                    |
# |--------------|---------------|-------------|------------|--------------------------|
# | Pushover     | $5 one-time   | Excellent   | 5 minutes  | Best for iOS/Android     |
# | ntfy.sh      | Free          | Good*       | 2 minutes  | *iOS requires app open   |
# | Twilio       | ~$25 + usage  | Excellent   | 1-7 days   | Real SMS, complex setup  |
# | Email-to-SMS | Free          | Poor        | 5 minutes  | Often blocked by carrier |
#
# Recommendation: Use Pushover. The $5 is worth it for reliable notifications.
#
# ================================================================
